        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/16946",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I'm sorry to say that again and again...\n\nBut the code doesn't work the way you think.\nTime and Date always depend on the timezone, the date and dst.\nAnd not on GMT or CET alone.\n\nThe problem you are seeing seems to be related to timezone and dst.\n\nPlease give us your \n* timezone\n* locale\n* used SVN version\n* OS\nfor detailed reproduction.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-09-24T16:51:10.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-09-24T16:51:10.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/16947",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=voxpelli",
                        "name": "voxpelli",
                        "displayName": "Pelle Wessman",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Oh, seems like I left out which timezone I'm in. Of course that matters to determine why this error occur - because I'm getting what the time is in my timezone when the time specified occurs at GMT 0.\n\nTo clarify what I want: I want Zend_Date to contain the same value that I specify and not to expect that I'm giving it a GMT time and I want it to be consistent and contain the very same value no matter if I define it as an array in the constructor or as separate function calls.\n\n# timezone\n+1 GMT I think it is, I'm not the best at timezones so perhaps +2 now during summertime or something.\n{code}date_default_timezone_set('Europe\/Stockholm');{code}\n\n# locale\n{code}\nsetlocale(LC_ALL, array('sve', 'swe'));\nZend_Locale_Format::setOptions(array('locale' => 'sv_SE'));\n{code}\n\n# used SVN version\nHmm, well I'm using the 1.0.1 release. I hope it's okay to submit issues anyway - I checked and didn't see any existing issue about this matter now r in the past.\n\n# OS\nSwedish XP SP2 under wish I'm running a rather new version of XAMPP with new versions of both Apache and PHP although not the newest.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=voxpelli",
                        "name": "voxpelli",
                        "displayName": "Pelle Wessman",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-09-24T17:17:14.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-09-24T17:17:14.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/16950",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I was able to reproduce a misinterpreted behaviour with the data you provided related to CET instead of CEST set.\n\nPlease check out SVN 6511 where this error is fixed and give us response.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-09-25T08:10:19.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-09-25T08:10:19.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/17009",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=voxpelli",
                        "name": "voxpelli",
                        "displayName": "Pelle Wessman",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I have tried that revision of Zend_Date and it worked correctly.\n\nI don't understand what \"related to CET instead of CEST set.\" really is meaning but I can tell for the record that now when I tested this it gave the same errors with the old file no matter if I set the timezone in my php-file or not. It worked correctly with this new file also no matter if I specified it in my php-file. On the other hand - it might be that those settings I make in the php-files alreade are made by default because of the language of my OS or something - I don't know, I'm just telling what I see.\n\nGood job solving this so fast btw. I'm sorry I couldn't test it earlier!",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=voxpelli",
                        "name": "voxpelli",
                        "displayName": "Pelle Wessman",
